  <prompt>
    Validate performance of all PCF controls against NFR requirements. Check bundle sizes
    are under 1MB, render times under 200ms, and API response times under 500ms.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer with expertise in performance testing and bundle optimization.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Performance metrics collected and validated against NFRs. Bundle sizes verified under 1MB.
    Success criteria SC-15 validated.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Performance is critical for user experience. PCF controls must render quickly and not
      bloat bundle sizes. API endpoints must respond within acceptable timeframes.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/events-and-workflow-automation-r1/spec.md - NFR requirements</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR: PCF render time &lt;200ms</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR: API response time &lt;500ms</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">SC-15: PCF bundles use platform libraries (&lt;1MB each)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">Platform libraries should not be bundled</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/pcf.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/PCF-V9-PACKAGING.md</file>
      <file>projects/events-and-workflow-automation-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Review NFR requirements from spec.md</step>
    <step order="2">Check bundle sizes for all 5 PCF controls</step>
    <step order="3">Verify each bundle is under 1MB (should be ~100-300KB with platform libs)</step>
    <step order="4">If bundle too large, check for accidentally bundled React/Fluent UI</step>
    <step order="5">Measure render times for each control using browser devtools</step>
    <step order="6">Verify render times under 200ms</step>
    <step order="7">Measure API response times for key endpoints</step>
    <step order="8">Verify API times under 500ms</step>
    <step order="9">Test push API with 100 records - verify performance acceptable</step>
    <step order="10">Document all performance metrics</step>
    <step order="11">Identify and fix any performance issues</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 065 status to âœ… completed</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Check bundle sizes</tool>
    <tool name="browser">Performance devtools</tool>
    <tool name="terminal">Run shell commands</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/events-and-workflow-automation-r1/notes/performance-validation-results.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given each PCF control, when bundle is measured, then size is under 1MB.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given each PCF control, when render time is measured, then it is under 200ms.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given Event API endpoints, when response time is measured, then it is under 500ms.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given push API with 100 children, when executed, then completes in reasonable time
      (under 10 seconds for 100 records).
    </criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Bundle size check:
    ```bash
    cd src/client/pcf/{ControlName}
    npm run build
    ls -la out/controls/{ControlName}/bundle.js
    # Should be < 1MB (1,000,000 bytes)
    ```

    If bundle is large (>500KB), likely causes:
    - React bundled instead of platform-library
    - Fluent UI bundled instead of platform-library
    - Unused imports not tree-shaken

    Render time measurement:
    - Chrome DevTools > Performance > Record
    - Look for "Scripting" time during control initialization
  </notes>

